For the last at least 6 years, this is what I sent to my bizarre best friend for Christmas. @coltonlhaynes and I share the common ground of not favoring physical gifts. Thus six years ago, when I asked @cherylbrown915 my mom to take a photo of me on their farm in Texas and send it to Colton  bc he loves farms and was alone on Xmas (I know😫) - she just sent him a silent 12 sec video unbeknownst to her- Never have I ever seen Colton in such pure joy. He thrives on non flattering awkward situations of me. 
He calls it his favorite gift of all time. He looks forward to it every year.
So on every morning of Dec 25th, this is where you will find me. Also my stepdad’s sigh in the 5th bc he is so annoyed we have to do this every year 🤣
Also my stepdad in the 6th getting more into it and wanting to be B camera for a different angle in front of Colton’s favorite fountain. 
Please enjoy my Christmas gifts to Colton for the last 6 years. 
He is also my first guest on the @howlerbacknowpodcast on @iheartradio where we discuss this very normal holiday tradition in our friendship.

This is my first film that I produced. I was a producer before I was an actor on this project. 

We are really proud of it. It’s been two years in the making and TRULY independent cinema is already a dying breed which is what this film is. We all believe in the theme of what this story reflects in the world and shines light on mother son relationships. I was honored to be brought on as a producer at the inception of this script before casting commenced. 

With that being said, to stand in solidarity with my fellow actors, I will no longer be posting about this film for the time being. We really hope you check it out July 21st.

We are so grateful to SAG 🙏 for not only protecting its members and fighting for fair compensation and contracts in this new age. They are also granting indie films the waivers to promote their films. We just got ours 🙏

It will only hurt for a second… See MOTHER MAY I? this Friday.

Tips to KiteSurfing! (From someone JUST starting) 
My first lesson was about 4 hours split up into two days 
where I master the look of a melting walrus wearing a life vest getting up on a wakeboard for the first time.

BUT! I digress- HERE IS WHAT I LEARNED at @airxkite school in Mandelieu la Napoule France- 

1. Leave your dignity at the door re: 👆 (kidding that’s actually my advice not theirs) 

2. They split up the board and the kite in your first lesson.
So for the first two hours I was just working with the kite in the water in an exercise called “body dragging”. 
(You also learn that pulling the kite bar towards you speeds you up and away from you slows you down- which cannn be very counter intuitive at first) enter 👉 my hair line fractured ankle (but not from this kite surfing trip). Again. Counter intuitive for a while folks!! Haha. You learn to get the hang of the kite while body dragging - that is until…

3. The next day you are on the wakeboard. I ironically found this easier than I thought it would be at least behind the boat although my stance is quite funny. Sit back and let the boat (or future kite) carry you up don’t try to pull. Once you put the two disciplines together there is yet another learning curve! But a really fun challenge that an injury won’t deter me from pursuing! 

Coming soon is my kite surfing my trip in Egypt! 

Let me know if you guys want to try kite surfing! or already have?! Then what are your favorite spots?!!

▪️1 egg
▪️1/4 cup of flour
▪️1/2 banana
▪️Pinch of cinnamon
▪️And literally too many blueberries. Just toss the whole grocery cart of blueberries in this dish (a whole small carton) and this will make enough for two people or one large meal for one!

Directions:
1. Stir all in a bowl and put on the skillet in little scoops
2. The best five minutes you will spend today!
